extra.remarks: Adi: "timings" is the main object in this unit. I am unclear whether a time unit alone evokes a scene, or otherwise should be marked as center. Based on our March meeting today, where we discussed that a production year of a film is scene evoking (usually in the wikicorpus), I have made this unit a scene.

next, whether "surgery visit" evokes one or two scenes. The phrase is mentioned in conglomeration; and within the scope of the unit they happen roughly at the same time, place and with roughly the same people. However, a more detailed imagination would distinguish between the time that the writer enters the practice and is greeted by reception staff until time of departure; to the interaction between the writer and surgeon, presumably in a surgery room.
